title: CASTLE ROCK Season 2 Episode 6 Breakdown, Theories, Easter Eggs, and Details You Missed!
author: Think Story
comment: Fetch me a glass of red wine as soon as I come out of that goo coffin! 🍷
Rita has the most depressing story! I feel for her terribly

I’m so glad they just got right to the point in this episode. No wasteful suspense dragging everything out just for another cliff hanger. Right away Rita was in CR, then she found Joy, told her the truth, Annie finds out, Rita finds Annie, Joy finds them both and seems to have chosen her side. Annie’s side. Til the next episode.
The scene of Annie drunk talking to Ace is a very good scene.
Season 1 was good but i felt like i had to convince myself. This season is just outstanding! every ep is just soooo packed with lore, twists, emotional moments. It has it all!
description:
In this video we take a deep dive and review episode 6 "The Mother" of Hulu's Castle Rock. We'll break down, review, and recap the episode while expanding on theories and Stephen King easter eggs!
